# cargo-fuzz generated artefacts
target/
artifacts/
coverage/
Cargo.lock

# Ignore all libfuzzer-generated corpus entries, EXCEPT permanent
# regression seeds — crashes / OOMs that a past fuzz run surfaced and
# a commit has since fixed. Tracking them in git ensures every future
# fuzz run (local, CI, post-clone) re-checks the exact input that
# triggered the original bug. Naming convention:
# `regression-<topic>-<YYYY-MM-DD>`.
#
# NOTE: we exclude `corpus/*/` at the subpath level (NOT `corpus/` at
# directory level) because git's gitignore can't re-include files
# inside an already-excluded directory.
corpus/*/*
!corpus/*/regression-*

# Known-crash quarantine: regression seeds whose source-side fix has NOT
# yet landed. Kept out of corpus/ so libfuzzer doesn't replay them on
# startup (which would exit 1 before any new exploration). Reproduce with
# `cargo +nightly fuzz run <target> known-crash/<target>/<file>`.
known-crash/
